/www.apple.com/iphone-se/specs/ |title = iPhone SE - Technical Specifications |website = Apple |language = en-US |access-date = April 15, 2020 }}</ref><br />W: {{convert|67.3|mm|in|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /><br />D: {{convert|7.3|mm|in|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| weight       = {{convert|148|g|oz|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| os           = [[iOS]] [[iOS 13|13]]\n<!-- | '''Original:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n<!-- | '''Current:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n<!-- | '''Last:''' For use ONLY after phone has been declared unsupported -->\n| soc          = [[Apple A13 Bionic]]<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| cpu          = \n| gpu          = \n| modem        = \n| memory       = 3 GB [[LPDDR|LPDDR4X]] [[Random-access memory|RAM]]<ref name=\"9to5mac 2\">{{cite web|last1=Mayo|first1=Benjamin|title=More iPhone SE specs: 3 GB RAM, 1821 mAH battery according to Chinese carrier tech specs|url=https://9to5mac.com/2020/04/16/iphone-se-battery-life-ram-specs/|website=9to5Mac|accessdate=April 16, 2020|date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| storage      = 64, 128, or 256 GB<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| memory_card  = \n| battery      = \n| charging     = Fast charging up to 18W<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /><br />[[Qi (standard)|Qi]] wireless charging<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| input        = \n| display      = {{convert|4.7|in|mm|abbr=on}} [[Retina display|Retina HD display]] with [[IPS panel|IPS]] technology, 1334 \u00d7 750 pixel resolution (326 [[pixels per inch|ppi]]), 1400:1 contrast ratio (typical)<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| ext_display  = \n| rear_camera  = 12MP, f/1.8 aperture, optical image stabilization, True Tone flash, autofocus<br />4K video recording at 24, 30, or 60 fps<br />1080p HD video recording at 30 or 60 fps<br />720p HD video recording at 30 fps<br />Cinematic video stabilization (4K, 1080p, and 720p)<br />Slo\u2011mo video support for 1080p at 120 or 240 fps<br />Portrait mode, Portrait lighting, and Smart HDR\n| front_camera = \n| sound        = \n| connectivity = [[Lightning (connector)|Lightning]] connector<br />Wi-Fi 6 ([[802.11ax]])<br>[[Bluetooth]] 5.0\n| other        = [[IP Code|IP67]] IEC standard 60529 (splash, water, and dust resistant)\n| sar          = \n| hac          = \n| website      = {{URL|www.apple.com/iphone-se/}}\n| references   = \n}}\n{{iPhone models}}\nThe '''second-generation iPhone SE''' is a [[smartphone]] designed, developed, and marketed by [[Apple Inc.]] It is part of the 13th generation of the [[iPhone]], alongside the [[iPhone 11]], [[IPhone 11 Pro|iPhone 11 Pro, and iPhone 11 Pro Max]]. Announced on April 15, 2020, the iPhone SE serves as a successor to both the [[iPhone SE (2016)|first-generation iPhone SE]] and the [[iPhone 8]].\n\nThe design of the iPhone SE is identical to the iPhone 8, but it uses the same [[Apple A13|A13 Bionic]] system-on-chip as the iPhone 11 lineup. Pre-orders will begin on April 17, with deliveries starting on April 24.<ref name=\"Official webpage\" />\n\n== History ==\nA successor to the first-generation iPhone SE has been rumored since 2017, a year after the device was released.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.macrumors.com/2017/11/22/iphone-se-2-release-date-first-half-2018/ |title = iPhone SE 2 Again Rumored to Launch in First Half of 2018 |website = MacRumors |language = en |access-date = April 15, 2020 }}</ref> The phone also had three other rumoured names: '''iPhone SE 2 / iPhone SE2''', '''iPhone''', and more recently, '''iPhone 9''', because this phone shares a design with the iPhone 8.\n\nIn March 2020, cases for the phone were reportedly being shipped to [[Best Buy]],<ref name=\"9to5mac\">{{Cite web |url = https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/ |title = iPhone 9 case inventory arriving at Best Buy, other retailers with April 5 merchandising date |last = Miller |first = Chance |date = March 30, 2020 |accessdate = April 3, 2020 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200403181051/https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/ |archive-date = April 3, 2020 |url-status = live }}</ref> showing an iPhone with an [[iPhone 8]]-sized body and a single camera lens.<ref name=\"9to5mac\" /> [[Belkin]] screen protectors for the iPhone SE were also listed on the online [[Apple Store]], cross-compatible with the iPhone 8 and iPhone 7. However, references to the iPhone SE were quickly removed.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.tomsguide.com/news/apple-iphone-9-will-be-the-new-iphone-se |title = iPhone 9 will be called iPhone SE and could launch soon (Update) |website = Tom's Guide |accessdate = April 3, 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"9to5mac\" />\n\n== Design ==\nThe iPhone SE features a design with an aluminum frame, and its front and back are made out of glass. The phone's external design and dimensions are nearly identical to that of the iPhone 8, except for a centered Apple logo and no iPhone branding. It features bezels on the top and bottom of the front and a home button integrated with second-generation [[Touch ID]].<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/ |title = iPhone SE 2020: Everything We Know |website = MacRumors |language = en |access-date = April 15, 2020 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180805112853/https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/ |archive-date = August 5, 2018 |url-status = live }}</ref>\n\nThe iPhone SE is available in three colors \u2014 white, black,<!-- colors are not proper nouns --> and [[Product Red|(Product) Red]], all of which have a black front.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /> Where this iPhone does deviate from the iPhone 8's design is with respect to the white model. Unlike the silver iPhone 8 (and all prior silver iPhones since the [[iPhone 4]]), the white iPhone SE features black bezels, bringing it into line with the color schemes of the [[iPhone 11 Pro]] and [[iPhone XR]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Color !!Name      <!-- hex codes from product selection page -->\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#1F2020\"| ||Black \n|-\n|bgcolor=\"F9F6EF\" |  ||White \n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#BA0C2E\"  |  ||Product Red\n|}\n\n== Specifications ==\n\n===Hardware===\nThe iPhone SE incorporates the Apple A13 Bionic system-on-chip (SoC) with an [[Apple motion coprocessors|M13 motion coprocessor]]. It is available in three internal storage configurations; 64&nbsp;GB, 128&nbsp;GB and 256&nbsp;GB.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" /> The SE has a rating of IP67 under [[IP Code|IEC standard 60529]] for dust and water resistance.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" /> \n\n==== Display ====\nThe iPhone SE features the same Retina HD display found on the iPhone 8. However, [[Force Touch|3D Touch]] is replaced by Haptic Touch.\n\n==== Camera ====\nThe iPhone SE features a single 12 MP rear camera similar to the wide camera of iPhone 11 and iPhone 11 Pro. The camera has a <!-- MOS:NOSYMBOLS -->f/1.8 aperture, autofocus, optical image stabilization, and a quad-LED True Tone flash. It is capable of recording 4K video at 24&nbsp;fps, 30&nbsp;fps, or 60&nbsp;fps, 1080p HD video at 30&nbsp;fps or 60&nbsp;fps, or 720p HD video at 30&nbsp;fps. The phone can also take panoramas up to 63&nbsp;MP, and is capable of shooting photos in burst mode.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" />\n\nThe front camera of the iPhone SE is a 7&nbsp;MP camera with f/2.2 aperture and autofocus, capable of shooting 1080p HD video at 30 fps.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" />\n\nBoth the front and rear cameras of the iPhone SE support Smart HDR, Portrait mode and Portrait Lighting.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" /> Unlike the iPhone 11 and 11 Pro, iPhone SE does not support Night mode.\n\n===Software===\nThe iPhone SE ships with [[iOS]] [[iOS 13|13]] and supports [[Apple Pay]].<!-- Apple Card is implicit with Apple Pay. --><ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n== Timeline of iPhone models ==\n{{Timeline of iPhone models}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat|iPhone SE (2020)}}\n* {{Official site|https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/}}\n\n{{iOS}}\n{{Apple hardware since 1998}}\n{{Apple Inc. hardware}}\n{{Apple}}\n[[Category:IPhone|*]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 2020]]\n[[Category:iOS]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2020]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the iPhone SE (2020)|its 2016 predecessor|iPhone SE (2016)|the general use of the term ''iPhone SE''|iPhone SE (disambiguation)}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name         = iPhone SE (2nd generation)\n| codename     = \n| logo         = IPhone SE (2nd generation) wordmark.svg\n| logosize     = <!-- include \"px\" - Uses users default image size if omitted -->\n| image        = IPhone SE (2nd generation) white vector.svg\n| imagesize    = \n| alt          = \n| caption      = iPhone SE in white\n| brand        = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| manufacturer = \n| slogan       = ''Lots to love. Less to spend.''<ref name=\"Official webpage\" >{{Cite web |url = https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/ |title = iPhone SE |website = Apple |language = en-US |access-date = April 15, 2020 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200415160521/https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/ |archive-date = April 15, 2020 |url-status = live }}</ref>\n| serieslabel  = [[History of iPhone|Generation]]\n| series       = 13th\n| modelnumber  = A2275<ref name=\"Official LTE networks\" >{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/iphone/LTE/|title=iPhone - View countries with supported LTE networks|website=Apple|language=en-US|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><br /> A2296<ref name=\"Official LTE networks\" /><br />A2298<ref name=\"Official LTE networks\" /> \n| networks     = \n| released     = {{Start date and age|2020|04|24}}\n| available    = <!-- Country {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} (Retailer) -->\n| discontinued = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| unitssold    = \n| unitsshipped = \n| predecessor  = [[iPhone SE (2016)|First-generation iPhone SE]]<br>[[iPhone 8]]\n| successor    =  \n| related      = [[iPhone 11]]<br>[[iPhone 11 Pro]]\n| type         = [[Smartphone]]\n| form         = Slate\n| size         = H: {{convert|138.4|mm|in|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications>{{Cite web |url = https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/specs/ |title = iPhone SE - Technical Specifications |website = Apple |language = en-US |access-date = April 15, 2020 }}</ref><br />W: {{convert|67.3|mm|in|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /><br />D: {{convert|7.3|mm|in|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| weight       = {{convert|148|g|oz|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| os           = [[iOS]] [[iOS 13|13]]\n<!-- | '''Original:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n<!-- | '''Current:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n<!-- | '''Last:''' For use ONLY after phone has been declared unsupported -->\n| soc          = [[Apple A13 Bionic]]<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| cpu          = \n| gpu          = \n| modem        = \n| memory       = 3 GB [[LPDDR|LPDDR4X]] [[Random-access memory|RAM]]<ref name=\"9to5mac 2\">{{cite web|last1=Mayo|first1=Benjamin|title=More iPhone SE specs: 3 GB RAM, 1821 mAH battery according to Chinese carrier tech specs|url=https://9to5mac.com/2020/04/16/iphone-se-battery-life-ram-specs/|website=9to5Mac|accessdate=April 16, 2020|date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| storage      = 64, 128, or 256 GB<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| memory_card  = \n| battery      = \n| charging     = Fast charging up to 18W<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /><br />[[Qi (standard)|Qi]] wireless charging<ref name=\"Official website: specifications 